mitism-on-campus%2Famp_articleshow%2F105224955.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fnew-york-university-is-sued-by-jewish-students-who-allege-anti-semitism-on-campus%2Famp_articleshow%2F105224955.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Fresh%20Nuclear%20Push%20May%20Be%20Different%20%E2%80%93%20But%20Questions%20Surround%20It%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15102249%2FBusiness-Units-Photo-Gallery-9.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20new%20nuclear%20push%20differs%20from%20its%20predecessors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20around%2C%20the%20country%20is%20not%20solely%20banking%20on%20its%20atomic%20establishment%20to%20erect%20an%20array%20of%20nuclear%20power%20plants.%20As%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2Fhow-india-is-shifting-its-nuclear-power-plans-into-high-gear%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20part%20of%20this%20series%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0showed%2C%20that%20approach%20resulted%20in%20cost-%20and%20time-overruns%2C%20and%20yielded%20an%20outcome%20where%20India%20missed%20every%20single%20deadline%20to%20boost%20its%20nuclear%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20bid%20to%20avoid%20that%20fate%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20new%20nuclear%20push%20stands%20on%20two%20new%20pillars.%20First%2C%20Nuclear%20Power%20Corporation%20of%20India%20will%20set%20up%20reactors%20in%20partnership%20with%20other%20state-owned%20companies%20like%20National%20Thermal%20Power%20Corporation.%20Second%2C%20the%20country%20is%20very%20bullish%20about%20Small%20and%20Modular%20Reactors%20(SMRs).%20These%2C%20goes%20the%20thinking%2C%20will%20be%20cheaper%20%3Cem%3Eand%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Efaster%20to%20construct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20claims%20%E2%80%93%20that%20NPCIL%E2%80%99s%20joint%20ventures%20or%20JVs%20will%20result%20in%20a%20faster%20rollout%2C%20and%20that%20SMRs%20will%20be%20competitive%20against%20rival%20forms%20of%20energy%20%E2%80%93%20have%20not%20received%20the%20broader%20scrutiny%20they%20deserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20JV%2C%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_7fe695-5c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20Ashvini%20deliver%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20JV%20between%20NPCIL%20and%20NTPC%20named%20Ashvini%20is%20neither%20new%20nor%20unique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20dates%20back%20to%20February%202016%20when%20the%20NDA%20government%20amended%20the%20Atomic%20Energy%20Act%20to%20enable%20NPCIL%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworld-nuclear.org%2Finformation-library%2Fcountry-profiles%2Fcountries-g-n%2Findia.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eform%20JVs%20with%20other%20PSUs%20for%20setting%20up%20nuclear%20power%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20here%20is%20that%20JV%20partners%20bring%20their%20investible%20surplus%20to%20the%20alliance%2C%20while%20NPCIL%20brings%20in%20nuclear%20know-how.%20The%20controlling%20stake%20%E2%80%93%20in%20what%20are%2051%3A49%20arrangements%20%E2%80%93%20would%20be%20with%20NPCIL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20then%20and%20now%2C%20NPCIL%20has%20formed%20JVs%20with%20NTPC%2C%20Indian%20Oil%20Corporation%2C%20and%20Nalco.%20%E2%80%9CJVs%20were%20also%20mooted%20with%20Hindustan%20Aluminium%20and%20Indian%20Railways%2C%20but%20those%20have%20stayed%20at%20a%20MoU%20level%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shah%20Nawaz%20Ahmad%2C%20who%20oversees%20India%20for%20the%20World%20Nuclear%20Association%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%2C%20the%20JV%20with%20NTPC%20seems%20to%20have%20made%20the%20most%20headway.%20NTPC%2C%20which%20will%20need%20to%20replace%20its%20coal%20fleet%20with%20cleaner%20alternatives%2C%20wants%20to%20install%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness%2Fcompanies%2Fntpc-to-have-2000-mw-nuclear-power-by-2032-and-20000-mw-by-2050-10068911.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2%20GW%20of%20nuclear%20energy%20by%202032%3B%204.2%20GW%20by%202035%3B%20and%2020%20GW%20by%202050%3C%2Fa%3E.%20SMRs%20are%20a%20part%20of%20its%20strategy.%20It%20wants%20to%20limit%20its%20JV%20with%20NPCIL%20to%20large%20reactors%20%E2%80%93%20and%20form%20a%20separate%20JV%20(where%20it%20is%20the%20majority%20partner)%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Farticleshow%2F96093087.cms%3Futm_source%3Dcontentofinterest%26utm_medium%3Dtext%26utm_campaign%3Dcppst%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20SMRs%20with%20private%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20media%20reports%2C%20it%20has%20assembled%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fpower-giant-ntpc-will-turn-to-nuclear-in-climate-goal-chase-11670474743551.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E15-member%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Mumbai%20to%20drive%20its%20nuclear%20ambitions.%20Beneath%20these%20announcements%20lie%20a%20mass%20of%20unknowns%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20JV%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20resolve%20the%20problems%20that%20have%20hamstrung%20nuclear%20power%20till%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20NTPC%20can%20raise%20funds%20more%20easily%20than%20NPCIL%2C%20as%20physicist%20MV%C2%A0Ramana%20writes%20in%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpenguin.co.in%2Fbook%2Fthe-power-of-promise%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Power%20of%20Promise%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20atomic%20establishment%20has%20never%20really%20struggled%20for%20cash.%20It%20has%20always%20been%20well-capitalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20about%20competitiveness%20against%20rival%20forms%20of%20energy%3F%20Unlike%20coal-based%20power%20plants%2C%20nuclear%20power%20has%20little%20or%20no%20running%20costs.%20Unlike%20solar%2C%20whose%20installation%20cost%20now%20stands%20at%20Rs%203%20crore%20to%20Rs%205%20crore%20per%20megawatt%20but%20panels%20start%20leaching%20efficiency%20after%2015%20or%20so%20years%2C%20nuclear%20plants%20have%20a%20much%20longer%20life.%20A%20better%20comparison%20is%20with%20hydel%20and%20pumped%20storage%20projects%20(PSPs).%20They%2C%20too%2C%20have%20high%20upfront%20costs%2C%20can%20be%20used%20for%20base%20load%20generation%20as%20well%20as%20grid%20balancing%2C%20and%20have%20low%20running%20costs%20%E2%80%93%20dams%20more%20so%20than%20pumped%20storage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20things%20get%20interesting.%20At%20NPCIL%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20nuclear%20power%20plant%20today%20ranges%20between%20Rs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-net-zero-renews-nuclear-power-push-with-small-modular-reactors-123051701102_1.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E-Rs%2015%20crore%2FMW.%20Imported%20reactors%20cost%20more.%20At%20Mithi%20Virdi%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20cost%20per%20MW%20for%20Westinghouse%20reactors%20has%20touched%20Rs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fcost-of-nuclear-power-proving-high-dae-in-a-fix%2Farticleshow%2F27920490.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E40%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20cost%2FMW%20for%20dams%20and%20PSPs%20(Rs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fnhpc-to-invest-1-40-1-76-trillion-in-pumped-hydropower-storage-projects-targeting-20-000-22-000-mw-capacity-11690134910628.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E7%20crore-Rs%208%20crore%2FMW%3C%2Fa%3E)%20is%20lower%20than%20that%20of%20nuclear%2C%20their%20costs%2Funit%20are%20similar%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Fpower%2Findia-to-consider-ways-to-lower-hydropower-tariffs%2Farticleshow%2F62599393.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E6%2Funit%20for%20a%20new%20dam%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20between%20Rs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness%2Fexclusive-government-to-invite-bids-for-green-ammonia-based-energy-storage-systems-11245641.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E5%2Funit%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Rs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pv-magazine-india.com%2F2023%2F04%2F27%2Fstrong-policy-focus-needed-to-drive-pumped-storage-development%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E9%2Funit%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20PSP%2C%20which%20incurs%20costs%20while%20pumping%20water%20back%20to%20the%20higher%20reservoir%3B%20and%20around%20Rs%207%2Funit%20for%20a%20reactor%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2FIndustry%2Fwhy-nuclear-when-india-has-an-ocean-of-energy%2Farticle28230036.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecosting%20between%20Rs%2015-20%20crore%2FMW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNuclear%E2%80%A6%20remains%20the%20dispatchable%20low-carbon%20technology%20with%20the%20lowest%20expected%20costs%20in%202025%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20IEA.%20%E2%80%9COnly%20large%20hydro%20reservoirs%20can%20provide%20a%20similar%20contribution%20at%20comparable%20costs%20but%20remain%20highly%20dependent%20on%20the%20natural%20endowments%20of%20individual%20countries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELand%20acquisition%20is%20one%20bugbear%20%E2%80%93%20but%20that%20applies%20to%20hydel%20and%20PSPs%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETechnical%20glitches%2C%20however%2C%20are%20a%20bigger%20risk.%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20has%20had%20hardly%20any%20standardisation%20of%20nuclear%20plants%20thus%20far%20and%20without%20standardisation%20nuclear%20cannot%20compete%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20senior%20official%20familiar%20with%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20clean%20energy%20plans%20told%20CarbonCopy%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%20The%20country%20has%20variously%20imported%20reactors%20from%20countries%20like%20France%2C%20Russia%20and%20the%20USA.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20what%20NTPC%20is%20trying%20to%20do%20now%E2%80%94develop%20standardised%20designs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20continues.%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20has%20valuable%20experience%20with%20the%20standardisation%20of%20coal%20boilers%20which%20greatly%20sped%20up%20projects.%20That%20is%20how%20the%20idea%20of%20Ashvini%20came%20about.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20thoughts%20echo%20those%20of%20former%20environment%20minister%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fblogs%2Fglobespotting%2Findia-needs-to-take-a-harder-look-at-its-nuclear-liability-law%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20an%20interview%20recently%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20should%20have%20standardised%20on%20its%20own%20design%20of%20a%20heavy%20water%20reactor.%20It%20should%20not%20depend%20on%20imported%20reactors.%20Two%20standard%20700%20MW%20reactors%20are%20coming%20up%20in%20Kakrapar%20and%20more%20elsewhere.%20India%20should%20standardise%20on%20those%20reactors.%20We%20should%20build%20on%20those%20reactors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%2C%20the%20current%20expansion%20hinges%20on%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1913854%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20700%20MW%20Pressurised%20Heavy%20Water%20Reactor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20Kakrapar%2C%20where%20this%20reactor%20was%20rolled%20out%2C%20it%20posted%20time-overruns%20on%20account%20of%20its%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcercind.gov.in%2F2018%2Forders%2F176.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CFirst%20Of%20a%20Kind%E2%80%9D%20Systems%20and%20delays%20in%20procuring%20critical%20equipment%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20time%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20unclear%20if%20the%20NTPC-NPCIL%20alliance%20has%20ironed%20out%20these%20glitches.%20CarbonCopy%20contacted%20both%20NTPC%20and%20NPCIL%20for%20interviews.%20They%20did%20not%20respond.%20Subsequently%2C%20questions%20were%20emailed%20to%20both%20companies.%20This%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20they%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurn%20to%20SMRs%20and%20similar%20questions%20intensify.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_119168-87%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESMRs%3A%20An%20idea%20whose%20time%20has%20come%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20time%20now%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20once%20renewables%E2%80%99%20prices%20began%20to%20drop%20%E2%80%93%20the%20nuclear%20industry%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20boost%20its%20own%20competitiveness.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20trying%20to%20bring%20down%20its%20costs%2C%20nuclear%20plants%20have%20bet%20on%20scale%2C%20spreading%20costs%20over%20a%20larger%20power%20output.%20With%20SMRs%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20heading%20the%20other%20way.%20Instead%20of%20building%20one%20large%20reactor%2C%20SMR%20makers%20want%20to%20mass-produce%20smaller%20reactors%2C%20and%20to%20use%20that%20scale%20to%20drive%20costs%20down.%20Modularity%20%E2%80%93%20where%20complete%20reactors%20are%20shipped%20out%20%E2%80%93%20is%20also%20expected%20to%20cut%20installation%20time%20and%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20take%20a%20large%20reactor%20like%20Kudankulam%2C%20on-site%20construction%20cost%20will%20be%20as%20much%20as%2030-40%25%20of%20the%20eventual%20cost%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Vinod%20Sahni%2C%20a%20former%20director%20of%20the%20Raja%20Ramanna%20Centre%20for%20Advanced%20Technology%20at%20BARC.%20With%20SMRs%2C%20says%20manufacturers%2C%20installation%20time%20will%20drop%20from%20five%20or%20more%20years%20to%20less%20than%20two.%20The%20NDA%20echoes%20these%20claims.%20SMRs%2C%20it%20says%2C%20will%20yield%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1879298%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esignificant%20savings%20in%20cost%20and%20construction%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20fast-track%20nuclear%20power%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20claims%20by%20SMR%20makers%20have%20been%20challenged%20by%20others%20%E2%80%93%20including%20the%20nuclear%20establishment%20itself.%20Can%20mass%20production%20drive%20down%20reactor%20prices%3F%20The%20answer%20to%20that%20question%20lies%20in%20a%20thicket%20of%20deeper%20questions.%20In%20any%20manufacturing%20process%2C%20raw%20material%20costs%20account%20for%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20costs.%20Efficiencies%20result%20from%20factors%20like%20cheaper%20sourcing%20of%20inputs%20by%20placing%20large%20orders%3B%20spreading%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20assembly%20plant%2C%20R%26amp%3BD%2C%20etc%2C%20over%20a%20larger%20output%3B%20and%20so%20on.%20And%20so%2C%20%C2%A0how%20many%20reactors%20will%20an%20assembly%20line%20need%20to%20produce%20to%20score%20meaningful%20savings%20on%20manufacturing%20costs%3F%20In%20a%20paper%20about%20the%20competitiveness%20of%20nuclear%20power%2C%20Ramana%20estimated%20the%20cost%2FMW%20of%20SMRs%20will%20match%20that%20of%20large%20reactors%20only%20after%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facee.princeton.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F06%2FAndlinger-Nuclear-Distillate-Article-6.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanywhere%20between%20700%20and%2060%2C000%20reactors%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%20been%20manufactured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20anywhere%20between%2040%20and%2070%20SMRs%20are%20in%20development%20across%20the%20world%2C%20how%20many%20reactors%20can%20each%20assembly%20line%20expect%20to%20manufacture%20each%20year%3F%20During%20installation%2C%20SMRs%20face%20the%20same%20risk%20as%20large%20reactors%E2%80%94of%20cost%20and%20time-overruns.%20Once%20installed%2C%20they%20produce%20the%20same%20externalities%20as%20large%20reactors%20(like%20accidents%20and%20radioactive%20waste%20disposal)%20and%2C%20ergo%2C%20have%20similar%20system%20costs%20as%20large%20reactors%20(boilers%2C%20turbines%2C%20safety%20systems%2C%20staff).%20All%20these%20costs%2C%20however%2C%20have%20to%20be%20recovered%20from%20lower%20power%20output.%20That%20will%20add%20to%20the%20cost%20per%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20whole%2C%20SMRs%20might%20be%20much%20costlier%20than%20large%20reactors.%20In%20his%20talk%20at%20the%20India%20Nuclear%20Business%20Platform%2C%20A.K.%20Nayak%2C%20head%20(Nuclear%20Control%20and%20Program%20Wing)%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Atomic%20Energy%2C%20pegged%20the%20%E2%80%9Cballpark%E2%80%9D%20cost%20of%20erecting%20an%20SMR%20at%20%E2%80%9CRs%20200%20million%2FMW%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20or%20Rs%2020%20crore%2FMW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20running%20cost%20might%20be%20higher%20as%20well.%20%E2%80%9CGiven%20their%20smaller%20size%2C%20SMRs%20have%20a%20greater%20surface%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Grover.%20%E2%80%9CWhich%20means%20greater%20neutron%20leakage%20and%20therefore%2C%20more%20spent%20fuel.%E2%80%9D%20This%20point%20has%20been%20made%20elsewhere%20as%20well.%20%E2%80%9CA%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.2111833119%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%20published%20in%20the%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20National%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0concluded%20that%20SMRs%20would%20create%20up%20to%2030%20times%20more%20radioactive%20waste%20per%20unit%20of%20electricity%20than%20conventional%20reactors%E2%80%9D%2C%20reported%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energymonitor.ai%2Fsectors%2Fpower%2Fsmall-modular-reactors-smrs-what-is-taking-so-long%2F%3Fcf-view%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEnergy%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EMonitor%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20about%20cost%20per%20unit%3F%20As%20IEEFA%20reported%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fieefa.org%2Fresources%2Feye-popping-new-cost-estimates-released-nuscale-small-modular-reactor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearlier%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CNuScale%E2%80%99s%20first%20power%20plant%E2%80%A6%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fthe-dream-of-mini-nuclear-plants-hangs-in-the-balance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreased%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20initial%20estimated%20electricity%20cost%20from%205.8%20cents%20per%20kWh%20to%208.9%20cents%20per%20KWh.%20That%20increase%20%5Ba%20jump%20from%20Rs%207.25%2Funit%20to%20Rs%2010.3%2Funit%5D%20would%20have%20been%20even%20higher%20if%20not%20for%20%244%20billion%20in%20federal%20tax%20subsidies%20and%20a%20%2430%2FMWh%20subsidy%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20the%20Australian%20energy%20think-tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20%E2%82%B910.3%2Funit%20(or%20more)%2C%20SMRs%20will%20be%20more%20expensive%20than%20pumped%20storage%20%E2%80%93%20which%20can%20also%20address%20intermittency%20and%20ensure%20grid%20stability.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20not%20sure%20SMRs%20are%20a%20fruitful%20LT%20investment%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20author%20Prabir%20Purkayastha.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20pumped%20storage%20is.%20You%20can%20use%20it%20to%20cycle%20up%20and%20down.%20You%20can%20create%20these%20in%20small%20areas.%20They%20can%20do%20daily%20balancing%20as%20well%20as%20long-term%20balancing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20these%20reasons%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20community%20is%20not%20convinced.%20%E2%80%9CNowhere%20in%20the%20world%20have%20SMRs%20been%20used%2C%E2%80%9D%20academic%20R.%20Rajaraman%20said%C2%A0in%20April.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20yet%20to%20see%20a%20proof%20of%20concept.%20It%E2%80%99s%20all%20ambitious%20talk%20and%20exaggerated%20claims.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20numbers%20%E2%80%93%20coupled%20with%20the%20absence%20of%20commercial%20models%20in%20the%20market%20and%20reluctance%20within%20the%20nuclear%20establishment%E2%80%94raise%20a%20large%20question.%20Support%20for%20SMR%20comes%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Findia-considering-allowing-foreign-investment-nuclear-power-sources-2023-05-05%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelsewhere%20in%20the%20government%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20DAE%20(Department%20of%20Atomic%20Energy)%20and%20Niti%20Aayog%2C%20some%20see%20SMRs%20as%20an%20opportunity%2C%E2%80%9D%20Grover%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20think%20SMRs%20can%20be%20deployed%20quickly%20and%20economically.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20this%20article%20was%20being%20finalised%2C%20news%20came%20too%20that%20NuScale%20had%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Fnuscale-power-uamps-agree-terminate-nuclear-project-2023-11-08%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterminated%20its%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0with%20Utah.%20%E2%80%9CNuScale%E2%80%99s%20Utah%20plant%20was%20expected%20to%20be%20the%20first%20SMR%20to%20win%20a%20license%20from%20the%20U.S.%20Nuclear%20Regulatory%20Commission%20for%20construction%2C%E2%80%9D%20reported%20Reuters.%20Concerns%20about%20uncompetitiveness%20were%20a%20major%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20writes%20itself.%20Why%20is%20India%20so%20bullish%20about%20an%20untested%20technology%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_800434-fc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20question%20of%20risk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20time%2C%20the%20world%20is%20seeing%20as%20many%20as%2070%20SMR%20models%20under%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNuScale%20is%20creating%20a%20small%20reactor%20by%20downsizing%20an%20existing%20reactor%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ahmad.%20%E2%80%9COthers%20are%20innovating%20new%20designs.%20In%20the%20next%20three%20to%20four%20years%2C%20an%20array%20of%20SMRs%20will%20be%20offered%20as%20the%20first%20of%20a%20kind.%20These%20will%20range%20from%20micro%20(200%20to%20500%20kw)%20to%20small%20(below%20300%20MW).%E2%80%9D%20(India%20has%20its%20own%20small%20reactor.%20This%20is%20the%20300%20MW%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barc.gov.in%2Freactor%2Fahwr.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAHWR300-LEU%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Developed%20by%20BARC%2C%20it%20runs%20on%20thorium%20and%20plutonium.%20It%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20modular).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20SMR%20makers%20are%20eyeing%20developing%20countries%20which%20need%20to%20decarbonise%20but%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20enough%20solar%2C%20wind%20and%20hydel%20potential%20to%20quit%20coal.%20Take%20NuScale.%20It%20hopes%20to%20build%20SMRs%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Fnuscale-power-uamps-agree-terminate-nuclear-project-2023-11-08%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERomania%2C%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Poland%20and%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20India.%20As%20Nayak%20said%20at%20his%20conference%3A%20India%20has%20to%20retrofit%2022O%20GW%20of%20thermal%20capacity.%20%E2%80%9CWith%20a%C2%A0ballpark%20figure%20of%20200%20Mn%20INR%2F%20MW%2C%C2%A0%20business%20has%20a%20potential%20of%20INR%2044%20Trillion%20(USD%20550%20Billion)%20over%20the%20next%2020%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Add%20industrial%20demand%20for%20SMRs%20and%20that%20number%20will%20swell%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20outcome%20is%20lobbying.%20At%20this%20time%2C%20a%20bevy%20of%20foreign%20SMR%20manufacturers%20%E2%80%93%20chiefly%20Westinghouse%2C%20Holtec%2C%20NuScale%2C%20Rosatom%20%E2%80%94%20are%20eyeing%20India.%20Hardwired%20into%20their%20lobbying%20is%20the%20worry%20that%20India%20might%20relax%20vital%20safeguards%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0invest%20billions%20in%20an%20uncompetitive%20source%20of%20electricity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20thermal%20power%20plants%20(TPP)%2C%20SMRs%20cannot%20be%20installed%20in%20seismic%20zones.%20This%20means%20NTPC%E2%80%99s%20TPPs%20around%20Delhi%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20cannot%20be%20retro-fitted.%20Also%2C%20nuclear%20reactors%20are%20required%20to%20have%20an%20exclusion%20zone%E2%80%94a%201.6%20km%20radius%E2%80%94around%20them.%20Most%20thermal%20power%20projects%2C%20however%2C%20have%20towns%20and%20villages%20pressing%20up%20against%20their%20walls.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20to%20install%20SMRs%2C%20NTPC%20will%20have%20to%20either%20acquire%20land%20for%20a%20safety%20zone%20around%20power%20plants%20being%20retro-fitted%20or%20the%20government%20will%20have%20to%20do%20away%20with%20this%20stipulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20is%20also%20soft-pedalling%20the%20civil%20liability%20issue.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20has%20been%20pushed%20to%20the%20backburner%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20senior%20government%20official.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20law%20but%20it%20is%20not%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20these%20discussions.%20It%20will%20not%20be%20a%20deal%20breaker.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20questions%20write%20themselves.%20Should%20nuclear%20or%20renewables%20and%20pumped%20storage%20take%20the%20base-load%3F%20How%20much%20nuclear%20power%20should%20India%20build%3F%20Should%20it%20focus%20on%20large%20reactors%20or%20SMRs%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20vital%20queries.%20To%20set%20up%2010%2C000%20MW%20of%20SMR%20capacity%2C%20India%20will%20need%20to%20spend%20Rs%20200%2C000%20crore.%20For%20this%20sum%2C%20it%20could%20set%20up%2016%2C000%20MW%20of%20large%20reactors.%20Or%2C%20at%20Rs%207.5%20crore%2FMW%2C%2025%2C000%20MW%20of%20pumped%20storage%20capacity.%20Alternately%2C%20should%20the%20country%20invest%20in%20smarter%20grids%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_fe7a57-e1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bigger%20question%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModern%20grid%20operators%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fe360.yale.edu%2Ffeatures%2Fthree-myths-about-renewable-energy-and-the-grid-debunked%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Ramana%20recently%2C%20are%20trying%20to%20create%20100%25%20renewable%20grids%20by%20addressing%20intermittency%20without%20falling%20back%20on%20%E2%80%9Cbaseload%E2%80%9D%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20and%20foremost%20is%20energy%20efficiency%2C%20which%20reduces%20demand%2C%20especially%20during%20periods%20of%20peak%20use%E2%80%A6.%20A%20second%20option%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frmi.org%2Finsight%2Fthe-economics-of-demand-flexibility-how-flexiwatts-create-quantifiable-value-for-customers-and-the-grid%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemand%20flexibility%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fa%3E%20wherein%20utilities%20compensate%20electricity%20customers%20that%20lower%20their%20use%20when%20asked%20%E2%80%93%20often%20automatically%20and%20imperceptibly%20%E2%80%93%20helping%20balance%20supply%20and%20demand.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20recent%20study%20found%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20U.S.%20has%20200%20gigawatts%20of%20cost-effective%20load%20flexibility%20potential%20that%20could%20be%20realised%20by%202030%20if%20effective%20demand%20response%20is%20actively%20pursued.%E2%80%9D%20Before%20embarking%20on%20the%20nuclear%20buildup%2C%20India%20needs%20tno%20ascertain%20the%20equivalent%20number%20for%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20and%20then%20see%20how%20much%20additional%20base%20load%20it%20needs.%20The%20costs%20of%20not%20doing%20so%20are%20stranded%20nuclear%20plants%20%E2%80%93%20or%20expensive%20power%20for%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20having%20those%20conversations%2C%20however%2C%20India%20is%20rushing%20to%20embrace%20SMRs.%20Not%20only%20does%20all%20this%20draw%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20ill-fated%20adventure%20with%20Enron%20to%20mind%2C%20it%20also%20highlights%20a%20larger%20flaw%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20climate%20change.%20As%20journalist%20Joydeep%20Gupta%20had%20commented%20in%20a%20recent%20article%20for%20%3Cem%3EThirdPole%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fclimate%2Fas-democracies-weaken-who-gets-say-south-asia-climate-future%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecrecy%20pervades%20South%20Asian%20countries%E2%80%99%20responses%20to%20climate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20nuclear%2C%20India%20is%20embarking%20on%20an%20expensive%20buildup%20%E2%80%93%20even%20thinking%20of%20retooling%20safety%20norms%20%E2%80%93%20without%20much%20of%20a%20discussion%20on%20viability%2C%20alternatives%20and%20attendant%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2Fa-jv-in-tow-will-indias-new-nuclear-push-work%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2F%5C%22%3ECarbon%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2F%5C%22%3ECopy%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Read%20part%20one%20of%20the%20series%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fhow-india-is-shifting-its-nuclear-power-plans-into-high-gear%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700024218000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15102249%2FBusiness-Units-Photo-Gallery-9.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fntpc-nuclear-power-corporation-npcil-smr%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22NPCIL%20is%20forming%20joint%20ventures%2C%20Niti%20Aayog%20is%20keen%20on%20Small%20and%20Modular%20Reactors.%C2%A0Why%20is%20India%20so%20bullish%20about%20an%20untested%20technology%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fntpc-nuclear-power-corporation-npcil-smr%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22K%20Kavitha%20On%20How%20Family%20Responds%20To%20Stress%20Due%20To%20Delhi%20Excise%20Case%20Probe%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20leader%20K%20Kavitha%2C%20being%20questioned%20in%20the%20Delhi%20excise%20policy%20case%2C%20spoke%20about%20how%20tough%20it%20is%20for%20her%20family%20every%20time%20the%20probe%20agency%20summons%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20a%20normal%20middle-class%20family.%20If%20one%20of%20the%20family%20member%20is%20missing%20for%20a%20certain%20time%2C%20it%20will%20be%20hard%20on%20everybody.%20Everybody%20was%20very%20anxious%2C%20very%20worried%2C%26quot%3B%20K%20Kavitha%20tells%20NDTV%20when%20asked%20about%20reports%20that%20she%20could%20be%20arrested%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20spoke%20about%20her%20sartorial%20choices%20and%20explained%20why%20she%20usually%20wears%20a%20saree.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20politician%2C%20it's%20my%20job%20to%20dress%20in%20a%20certain%20way%2C%20for%20people%20to%20feel%20that%20I%20am%20one%20among%20them%20and%20they%20can%20approach%20me.%20I%20am%20not%20dressed%20differently%20from%20any%20person%20on%20the%20street%2C%20which%20is%20why%20they%20come%20up%20to%20me%20and%20talk%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKavitha%2C%20daughter%20of%20Telangana%20Chief%20Minister%20