cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Two%20Weeks%20After%20Myanmar%20Rebels'%20Offensive%2C%20Junta%20Struggles%20to%20Mount%20Counterattack%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F12153337%2F2021_Myanmar_Armed_Forces_Day_05-e1699949248972.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20more%20than%2010%20days%20since%20the%20Brotherhood%20Alliance%20launched%20its%20Operation%201027%20in%20northern%20Shan%20State%20in%20eastern%20Myanmar.%20Thus%20far%2C%20junta%20boss%20Min%20Aung%20Hlaing%20has%20only%20been%20able%20to%20issue%20verbal%20threats%20to%20strike%20back%20at%20the%20tripartite%20military%20alliance%20made%20up%20of%20the%20Myanmar%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20Army%20(MNDAA)%2C%20the%20Ta%E2%80%99ang%20National%20Liberation%20Army%20(TNLA)%20and%20the%20Arakan%20Army%20(AA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiggest%20challenge%20since%20coup%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regime%20lost%20around%20100%20outposts%20in%20a%20week%2C%20and%20the%20ethnic%20alliance%20seized%20a%20haul%20of%20weapons.%20The%20junta%E2%80%99s%20bases%20in%20Kunlong%2C%20Monekyat%2C%20Nanbeng%20(on%20Lashio-Tangyan%20Road)%20and%20Monekoe%20were%20the%20only%20ones%20that%20managed%20to%20resist%20the%20offensive%2C%20with%20the%20regime%20losing%20most%20of%20its%20outposts%20in%20the%20area%20with%20a%20speed%20no%20one%20previously%20imagined%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regime%20has%20also%20lost%20at%20least%20six%20tanks%20and%20armoured%20vehicles%2C%20and%20the%20Myanmar%20military%20has%20admitted%20it%20no%20longer%20has%20control%20of%20Chin%20Shwe%20Haw%2C%20Pansai%20and%20Phaung%20Sai%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ethnic%20alliance%20has%20taken%20control%20of%20Hsenwi%20north%20of%20the%20Namtu%20River%2C%20but%20junta%20troops%20maintain%20a%20defensive%20position%20south%20of%20the%20river.%20Some%20junta%20outposts%20have%20fallen%20in%20Monekoe%2C%20but%20the%20junta%20hill-top%20outpost%20that%20houses%20the%20tactical%20command%20remains%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommunication%20networks%20in%20northern%20Shan%20state%20have%20been%20disrupted%2C%20border%20trade%20through%20the%20105th%20Mile%20Camp%2C%20Muse%2C%20Jinsanjiao%20and%20Chin%20Shwe%20Haw%20has%20halted%2C%20and%20junta%20government%20employees%20have%20fled%20their%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regime%20has%20only%20been%20able%20to%20maintain%20its%20administrative%20mechanism%20in%20Lashio%2C%20Hsipaw%2C%20Tangyan%2C%20Hopan%20and%20Panlong%2C%20and%20has%20lost%20control%20of%20many%20towns%20including%20Chin%20Shwe%20Haw%2C%20Kunlong%2C%20Hsenwi%2C%20Kutkai%2C%20Muse%2C%20Pansai%2C%20Paungsai%2C%20Kyaukme%20and%20Nawngkhio%20in%20northern%20Shan%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FX6JLclv7Yvg%3Fsi%3D7DgrumQg7PdaI7NF%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMyanmar%20military%E2%80%99s%20response%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Myanmar%20military%20has%20airlifted%20reinforcements%20to%20Lashio%20and%20Kunlong%20as%20well%20as%20to%20the%2016th%20Military%20Operations%20Command%20in%20the%20south%20of%20Hsenwi.%20It%20is%20also%20airlifting%20and%20parachuting%20food%20supplies%20and%20ammunition%20to%20its%20outposts%20in%20northern%20Shan%20state%20that%20have%20been%20cut%20off%20by%20the%20ethnic%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20dispatched%20some%20combat%20forces%20including%20tank%20units%20from%20Pyin%20Oo%20Lwin%20in%20Mandalay%20region%20to%20attack%20Nawnghkio%20in%20northern%20Shan%2C%20but%20the%20reinforcements%20were%20intercepted%20by%20combined%20forces%20of%20the%20Mandalay%20People%E2%80%99s%20Defense%20Force%20and%20the%20TNLA%20and%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20advance%20to%20the%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regime%20is%20still%20struggling%20to%20mount%20a%20counterattack%20nearly%20two%20weeks%20after%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20offensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOperation%201027%20has%20again%20highlighted%20the%20Myanmar%20military%E2%80%99s%20serious%20shortage%20of%20personnel.%20Junta%20reinforcements%20airlifted%20to%20Lashio%20come%20from%20southern%20Shan%20and%20Kayah%20(or%20Karenni)%20states.%20The%20troops%20dispatched%20from%20Pyin%20Oo%20Lwin%20are%20from%20the%20101st%20Light%20Infantry%20Division%20based%20in%20Pakokku%20but%20number%20less%20than%20150%2C%20and%20it%20is%20very%20unlikely%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20repulse%20the%20resistance%20attacks%20and%20push%20their%20way%20through%20to%20Nawnghkio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regime%20is%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20bring%20in%20as%20many%20reinforcements%20as%20it%20would%20like%20into%20northern%20Shan%20state.%20Fighting%20a%20multi-front%20war%20in%20Kachin%2C%20Karen%20and%20Chin%20states%20and%20Magwe%2C%20Sagaing%2C%20Mandalay%2C%20Bago%20and%20Tanintharyi%20regions%2C%20it%20might%20not%20want%20to%20risk%20new%20fronts%20in%20Rakhine%20and%20southern%20Shan%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%2085vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14174638%2FOperation-1027.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14174638%2FOperation-1027.png%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14174638%2FOperation-1027-300x226.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684757%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22376%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMap%20of%20Operation%201027%20as%20of%20early%20November.%20Gains%20made%20by%20the%20Brotherhood%20Alliance%20in%20green.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommons.wikimedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFile%3AOperation_1027.svg%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Clyde%20H.%20Mapping%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%3C%2Fa%3E%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERakhine%20State%20is%20home%20to%20the%20AA%2C%20which%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Brotherhood%20Alliance%2C%20while%20the%20Shan%20State%20Progress%20Party%20(SSPP)%2C%20an%20ally%20of%20the%20Brotherhood%20Alliance%2C%20has%20a%20strong%20presence%20in%20southern%20Shan%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Kachin%20(Kachin%20Independence%20Army)%2C%20Ta%E2%80%99ang%20(TNLA)%20and%20Kokang%20(MNDAA)%20ethnic%20armed%20groups%20having%20seized%20one%20area%20after%20another%20in%20northern%20Shan%20state%2C%20the%20SSPP%20might%20not%20be%20willing%20to%20just%20sit%20and%20watch%20on%20the%20sidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20while%20the%20AA%20has%20openly%20admitted%20that%20it%20is%20involved%20in%20fighting%20not%20only%20in%20Kachin%20but%20also%20in%20northern%20Shan%20state%20and%20Sagaing%20region%2C%20the%20regime%20has%20blamed%20the%20KIA%2C%20MNDAA%20and%20TNLA%20for%20the%20offensives%20but%20has%20not%20said%20a%20single%20word%20about%20the%20AA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Myanmar%20military%20once%20refused%20to%20allow%20the%20AA%20to%20participate%20in%20national-level%20peace%20talks%20known%20as%20the%20Union%20Peace%20Conference%2C%20demanded%20its%20disarmament%20and%20forced%20the%20then-civilian%20government%20%E2%80%93%20which%20it%20later%20ousted%20%E2%80%93%20to%20declare%20it%20a%20terrorist%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20its%20unwillingness%20to%20complain%20about%20the%20Rakhine%20ethnic%20armed%20group%20now%20is%20an%20indication%20that%20the%20Myanmar%20military%20dreads%20opening%20a%20new%20front%20in%20Rakhine%2C%20and%20is%20short%20of%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regime%2C%20apparently%20also%20concerned%20that%20the%20United%20Wa%20State%20Army%20and%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20Army%20%E2%80%93%20political%20allies%20of%20the%20Brotherhood%20Alliance%20%E2%80%93%20will%20join%20the%20offensive%2C%20recently%20re-blocked%20roads%20between%20Mongla%20and%20Kengtung.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20reportedly%20arranging%20to%20gather%20around%2020%20battalions%2C%20or%20over%2020%2C000%20troops%2C%20to%20strike%20back%20against%20Operation%201027.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fno-end-in-sight-the-continuing-conflict-in-myanmar-two-years-after-military-coup%5C%22%3ENo%20End%20in%20Sight%3A%20The%20Continuing%20Conflict%20in%20Myanmar%20Two%20Years%20After%20Military%20Coup%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20combined%20forces%20of%20the%20Brotherhood%20Alliance%2C%20People%E2%80%99s%20Defense%20Force%2C%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army%20and%20Burma%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army%20currently%20fighting%20in%20northern%20Shan%20State%20total%20around%2020%2C000.%20So%2C%20the%20regime%20needs%20to%20mobilise%20at%20least%2020%2C000%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20escalating%20fighting%20in%20Kachin%2C%20Karen%2C%20Kayah%20and%20Chin%20states%20and%20Sagaing%2C%20Magwe%2C%20Mandalay%20and%20Bago%20regions%20means%20the%20regime%20will%20likely%20not%20be%20able%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20fighting%20has%20changed%20in%20Sagaing%20and%20Magwe%20regions%2C%20with%20resistance%20forces%20now%20aiming%20to%20seize%20towns%20and%20more%20strategic%20junta%20bases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20well%20beyond%20what%20the%20junta%E2%80%99s%20air%20force%20can%20handle%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20its%20ground%20reinforcements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20the%20Myanmar%20military%20has%20told%20its%20troops%20manning%20smaller%20outposts%20to%20retreat%20and%20join%20bigger%20strongholds.%20It%20is%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20take%20back%20control%20of%2