him%20a%20%E2%80%9Cscapegoat%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20observations%20on%20the%20plea%20for%20suspension%20of%20his%20sentence%2C%20the%20tribunal%20raised%20serious%20questions%20on%20the%20court%20martial%20proceedings%2C%20calling%20its%20findings%20as%20%E2%80%9Cperverse%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cimproper%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20our%20considered%20view%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20considering%20the%20application%20for%20suspension%20of%20sentence%20and%20bail%2C%20the%20prima%20facie%20assessment%20by%20us%20is%20sufficient%20enough%20to%20prima%20facie%20come%20to%20a%20conclusion%20that%20the%20finding%20recorded%20in%20the%20trial%20is%20not%20proper%20and%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20perverse%20and%20improper%20finding%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20tribunal%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribunal%20observed%20that%20evidence%20relied%20upon%20during%20the%20court%20martial%20proceedings%20is%20not%20convincing%20enough%20to%20hold%20the%20captain%20guilty%20of%20the%20charges%20levelled%20against%20him.%20%E2%80%9CPrima%20facie%2C%20based%20on%20the%20material%20available%2C%20we%20are%20convinced%20that%20the%20likelihood%20of%20the%20captain%20being%20acquitted%20after%20hearing%20this%20appeal%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribunal%20bench%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20the%20findings%20recorded%20by%20it%20are%20only%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20adjudicating%20the%20plea%20for%20suspension%20of%20sentence%20and%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20not%20cause%20any%20prejudice%20to%20any%20of%20the%20parties%20at%20the%20time%20of%20trial.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthree-militants-killed-in-shopian-encounter-were-ordinary-labourers-families-allege%5C%22%3EThree%20%E2%80%98Militants%E2%80%99%20Killed%20in%20Shopian%20%E2%80%98Encounter%E2%80%99%20Were%20Ordinary%20Labourers%2C%20Families%20Allege%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuestions%20on%20statements%20of%20accused%20and%20witnesses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribunal%20found%20that%20the%20confessional%20statement%20of%20the%20captain%20during%20the%20court%20of%20inquiry%20%E2%80%93%20when%20he%20was%20in%20close%20arrest%20%E2%80%93%20was%20not%20recorded%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20requirements%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20captain%20recorded%20by%20the%20Board%20of%20Officers%20was%20in%20breach%20of%20different%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20our%20considered%20view%2C%20heavy%20reliance%20has%20been%20placed%20by%20the%20SGCM%20%5Bsummary%20general%20court%20martial%5D%20on%20the%20confession%20statement%20of%20the%20applicant%20recorded%20by%20the%20Board%20of%20Officers%20during%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20CoI%20and%20at%20the%20time%20the%20applicant%20was%20in%20close%20arrest.%20In%20our%20considered%20view%2C%20the%20confession%20statement%20recorded%20by%20the%20Board%20of%20Officers%20is%20in%20clear%20violation%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eto%20the%20requirement%20of%20section%2027%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%2C%20so%20also%20in%20breach%20of%20sections%2024%2C%2025%20and%2026%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20tribunal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20raised%20questions%20on%20the%20validity%20of%20statements%20made%20by%20Bilal%20Ahmad%20Lone%20and%20discarding%20of%20the%20statement%20of%20Tabish%20Nazir%20Lone%2C%20during%20the%20trial.%20Both%20Bilal%20and%20Tabish%20were%20Army%20informants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribunal%20said%20that%20the%20confession%20statement%20of%20Bilal%20Ahmad%20Lone%2C%20who%20was%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20case%20but%20turned%20an%20approver%20and%20has%20been%20pardoned%20by%20the%20chief%20judicial%20magistrate%20Shopian%2C%20cannot%20be%20used%20for%20convicting%20the%20captain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRelying%20upon%20the%20statement%20of%20a%20co-accused%2C%20in%20our%20considered%20view%2C%20and%20further%2C%20is%20in%20breach%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20section%2027%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20wherein%20it%20has%20been%20stipulated%20that%20based%20on%20the%20statement%20of%20a%20co-accused%2C%20a%20conviction%20cannot%20be%20ordered%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20tribunal%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20questioned%20the%20discarding%20of%20the%20statement%20of%20Tabish%20Nazir%20Lone%2C%20who%20turned%20hostile%2C%20during%20the%20trial%2C%20saying%20it%20becomes%20creditworthy%20and%20can%20be%20relied%20upon%20when%20read%20along%20with%20material%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22'They%20Were%20Poor%20Men'%3A%20Locals%20Question%20Army%20Version%20on%20Shopian%20'Encounter'%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fkashmir-shopian-encounter-army-version-questioned%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98They%20Were%20Poor%20Men%E2%80%99%3A%20Locals%20Question%20Army%20Version%20on%20Shopian%20%E2%80%98Encounter%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECO%E2%80%99s%20statement%20of%20being%20unaware%20%E2%80%98totally%20untrustworthy%2C%20highly%20doubtful%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20the%20situation%20report%20(SITREP)%20prepared%20by%20the%20Army%20and%20expenditure%20of%20arms%20and%20ammunition%2C%20the%20tribunal%20said%20that%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20commanding%20officer%20of%20the%2062%20Rashtriya%20Rifles%20that%20he%20was%20totally%20unaware%20of%20the%20event%20seems%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Ctotally%20untrustworthy%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Chighly%20doubtful%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccannot%20be%20believed%20on%20its%20face%20value%E2%80%9D%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribunal%2C%20in%20its%20view%2C%20said%20that%20there%20cannot%20be%20any%20motive%20for%20the%20captain%20to%20conduct%20such%20an%20operation%20without%20the%20knowledge%20of%20the%20commanding%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20noted%20that%20perusal%20of%20statements%20of%20some%20prosecution%20witnesses%20%E2%80%9Cthrow%20some%20light%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20prior%20information%20of%20the%20operation%20and%20permission%20from%20the%20CO%20was%20available%20and%20there%20was%20also%20sharing%20of%20location%20including%20deletion%20of%20chat%20from%20%5BW%5Dhatsapp%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20captain%2C%20in%20his%20appeal%2C%20has%20claimed%20that%20sequence%20of%20events%20shared%20in%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20of%20the%20company%20and%20the%20battalion%20were%20deleted%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20Court%20of%20Inquiry%20was%20ordered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fshopian-encounter-army%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Give%20Me%20His%20Body%E2%80%99%3A%20Father%20Insists%20Young%20Man%20Killed%20in%20Shopian%20%E2%80%98Encounter%E2%80%99%20Was%20Innocent%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExpenditure%20of%20arms%20and%20retaliatory%20firing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AFT%20said%20that%20exorbitant%20expenditure%20of%20arms%20and%20ammunition%2C%20as%20indicated%20in%20the%20situation%20report%2C%20discredits%20the%20case%20of%20prosecution%20to%20a%20large%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribunal%20said%20that%20the%20situation%20report%20and%20statements%20of%20some%20witnesses%20indicated%20retaliatory%20firing%20on%20the%20Army%20which%20had%20visited%20the%20place%20for%20the%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20contacted%2C%20advocate%20Sudhanshu%20S.%20Pandey%2C%20counsel%20for%20Bhoopendra%20Singh%2C%20said%20that%20their%20stand%20is%20vindicated%20because%20the%20summary%20general%20court%20martial%20had%20not%20followed%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbasic%20principles%20of%20criminal%20justice%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20highly%20grateful%20to%20the%20court%20for%20delivering%20justice%20to%20the%20young%20officer%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20feel%20they%20have%20been%20killed%20again%3A%20Families%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20families%20of%20the%20victims%20registered%20their%20shock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20another%20July%2018%20%5Bthe%20day%20when%20the%20three%20were%20killed%20in%202020%5D%20for%20us.%20I%20feel%20that%20they%20have%20killed%20our%20children%20for%20the%20second%20time.%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20believe%20it%20when%20someone%20from%20Srinagar%20informed%20me%20over%20phone%20yesterday%20that%20the%20accused%20has%20been%20released%20from%20the%20jail%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yosouf%2C%20father%20of%20Ibrar%20Ahmed%20(25)%2C%20one%20of%20the%20three%20civilians%20who%20had%20been%20killed%20in%20Amshipora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20relieved%20after%20the%20captain%20was%20sentenced%20to%20life%20imprisonment%20but%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20sleep%20last%20night%20after%20hearing%20that%20he%20had%20been%20released.%20I%20will%20do%20whatever%20is%20required%20to%20get%20justice%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F15183949%2Fabrar.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22798%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F15183949%2Fabrar.png%20798w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F15183949%2Fabrar-300x158.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-473362%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22421%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E16-year-old%20Mohammad%20Abrar.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFifty-year-old%20Bagga%20Khan%2C%20father%20of%2016-year-old%20Muhammad%20Abrar%20Ahmed%2C%20one%20of%20the%20victims%2C%20termed%20the%20verdict%20a%20grave%20injustice%20with%20the%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEveryone%20promised%20that%20justice%20will%20be%20done%20with%20us%20after%20they%20came%20to%20know%20that%20those%20killed%20were%20innocent%20civilians.%20Is%20it%20justice%3F%20We%20will%20fight%20for%20them%20till%20the%20last%20breath%20of%20life%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fshopian-encounter-mohammad-abrar-army-jk-police%5C%22%3EAs%20reported%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20then%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20August%2015%2C%202020%2C%20young%20Abrar%20had%20gone%20to%20Shopian%20to%20work%20as%20labourer%20in%20the%20orchards%20to%20earn%20money%20for%20his%20Class%2010%20admission%20fee%20and%20books.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDisappearance%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20of%20trio%2C%20Army%E2%80%99s%20claims%2C%20police%E2%80%99s%20probe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbrar%2C%20Imtiyaz%20and%20Ibrar%20disappeared%20in%20Shopian%20area%20of%20southern%20Kashmir%20on%20the%20intervening%20night%20of%20July%2018%20and%2019.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20the%20Army%20claimed%20to%20have%20killed%20three%20unidentified%20militants%20in%20a%20gunfight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20day%20later%2C%20Brigadier%20Ajay%20Katoch%2C%20commander%20of%2012%20Sector%20Rashtriya%20Rifles%20claimed%20that%20the%20Army%20had%20received%20%E2%80%9Chuman%20intelligence%20inputs%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20presence%20of%20four%20to%20five%20unidentified%20militants%20in%20Amshipora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20that%20the%20Army%20personnel%20came%20under%20fire%20twice%20from%20the%20militants%20before%20they%20were%20neutralised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20on%20August%2010%2C%202020%2C%20three%20families%20from%20Rajouri%20district%20of%20Jammu%20province%20claimed%20that%20those%20kil